{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6b890bc3-c884-46ee-99eb-0e357f88be79","content":"Here's the migrated command and the required setup:\n\n**Command:**\n```bash\ndotnet test --filter \"Category=Integration\" \\\n  -- \\\n  --report-trx \\\n  --collect-code-coverage \\\n  --crashdump \\\n  --hangdump --hangdump-timeout 5m\n```\n\nEverything after `--` is passed to Microsoft.Testing.Platform directly.\n\n**Required NuGet packages** (add to your test project):\n\n| Old capability | Package to add |\n|---|---|\n| `--logger trx` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.TrxReport` |\n| `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` | `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` |\n| `--blame-crash` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.CrashDump` |\n| `--blame-hang` | `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HangDump` |\n\n**To get Cobertura format** specifically, add a `.cobertura.config` or pass `--report-cobertura` (depending on the `Microsoft.CodeCoverage` version). With recent versions the default output already includes Cobertura; check your version's docs.\n\n**Key differences from the old command:**\n- `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (after `--`)\n- `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect-code-coverage`\n- `--blame-crash` → `--crashdump`\n- `--blame-hang` / `--blame-hang-timeout` → `--hangdump` / `--hangdump-timeout`\n- `--filter` stays before `--` and still uses the same syntax","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9be2a0ec-d923-41de-9cbb-aa4d9799b2fd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating their CI test command from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform (MSTest runner) on .NET 8. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing tooling, not a codebase task. Let me provide the answer directly.\n\nKey changes when moving to Microsoft.Testing.Platform:\n\n1. `dotnet test` still works but the underlying runner changes\n2. `--filter` → `--filter` (same, but can also use `--treenode-filter`)\n3. `--logger trx` → `--report-trx` (built-in)\n4. `--collect \"Code Coverage;Format=cobertura\"` → `--collect code-coverage` with Microsoft.CodeCoverage package, or you configure it differently\n\n\n5. VSTest-specific blame options like `--blame-crash` and `--blame-hang` aren't directly supported in the new platform, though you can run the test executable directly for more control\n\nWith Microsoft.Testing.Platform, the command-line interface shifts when using `dotnet test`, but there's flexibility in how you configure filtering, reporting, and coverage depending on which NuGet extensions you add to your project.\n\nWhen invoking via `dotnet test`, you pass platform-specific options after `--`, whereas running the test executable directly gives you access to the full set of options without the wrapper layer. I need to identify which NuGet packages provide each of the platform-specific options, then clarify how the command structure works with the `--filter` parameter and code coverage format configuration. I'm realizing the treenode filter syntax is specific to Microsoft.Testing.Platform, but when using `dotnet test`, the standard `--filter` flag works fine before the `--` separator. So the practical command would use the simpler Category filter with all the required diagnostic extensions enabled through command-line flags, assuming the NuGet packages are already added to the project.","outputTokens":1694,"requestId":"0841:16A6CA:7F513AF:8D866C1:69EABE7A"},"id":"9bc4c3c2-fc96-4df1-a595-66cc72368714","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:51:36.372Z","parentId":"1eed18d6-2d0d-467e-9d1b-3879def7b78e"}
